Cases in various countries not mentioned above or more recent case numbers

Caribbean locally acquired
---
Dominica (national). 26 Feb 2015. (reported) 3764 cases, (conf.) 173 cases. Outbreak officially declared over with no new cases in over 2 maximum incubation periods.
http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/latestnews/Dominica-CHIKV-epidemic-officially-over---Health-Ministry

Haiti (national). 3 Mar 2015. (reported) 64 695 cases.
http://www.trinidadexpress.com/news/303-cases-of-ChikV-in-TT-294931231.html

Jamaica (national). 3 Mar 2015. (reported) 39 new cases for 2015; for 2014 (reported) 4979; deaths 2014 to 19 Feb 2015 (susp.) 11, (conf.) 2.
http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/news/Chik-V-not-through-with-Jamaica-yet

Trinidad and Tobago. 3 Mar 2015. (reported) as of 28 Feb 2015, 303 cases.
http://www.trinidadexpress.com/news/303-cases-of-ChikV-in-TT-294931231.html

Mexico and Central America probable local transmission
---
Mexico (Guerrero state). 3 Mar 2015. (conf.) 43 cases. Municipality most affected: Acapulco 21 cases.
http://notimundo.com.mx/confirman-chikungunya-en-guerrero-con-43-casos/ [in Spanish]

[Acapulco is a very popular tourist destination. One hopes that control measures are effective to reduce the incidence and not discourage tourists from coming. - Mod.TY]

Costa Rica (national). 26 Feb 2015. (reported) more than 100 cases, 70 of which are locally acquired.
http://www.ticotimes.net/2015/02/26/honduras-registers-first-death-from-chikungunya-virus

Honduras (national). 26 Feb 2015. (conf.) 12 090 cases; deaths 1, a 23-day-old infant from Olancho department.
http://www.proceso.hn/salud-y-sociedad/item/97571-honduras-contabiliza-m%E1s-de-12-mil-casos-de-chikungunya.html

This report is confusing in that it states that the monthly average of cases for the 1st 2 months of 2015 is 3379 cases and the total so far for 2015 is more than 6758. Perhaps this represents the difference between confirmed and reported cases. A 6 Mar 2015 report indicates that there are at least 14 000 cases since the beginning of the outbreak and an average of 1000 cases weekly currently. (http://www.elheraldo.hn/pais/819133-331/piden-declara-alerta-por-dengue-y-chikungunya in Spanish). - Mod.TY]

Nicaragua (national). 26 Feb 2015. (conf.) nearly 4000 cases since July 2014.
http://elmundo.com.sv/nicaragua-registra-casi-4-000-casos-positivos-de-virus-chikunguna/ [in Spanish]

South America with ongoing transmission
---
Bolivia (Santa Cruz de la Sierra city, Santa Cruz department). 2 Mar 2015. (reported) cases increased from 44 to 51 in one month. Health alert declared.
http://www.sinembargo.mx/02-03-2015/1268483 [in Spanish]

Brazil
- National (week 06 ending 14 Feb 2015). (susp.) 418 cases, (conf.) 2768 cases. States most affected: Bahia 654 cases, Amapa 93 cases, Federal District 10 cases, Mato Grosso do Sul 9 cases.
http://portalsaude.saude.gov.br/images/pdf/2015/fevereiro/25/2015-006---Boletim-Dengue-SE06-2015.pdf [in Portuguese]

[Obviously, the case numbers have grown since this report was issued. - Mod.TY]

- Oiapoque, Amapa state. (reported) as of 25 Feb 2015, 2137 cases. Municipal state of health emergency declared.
http://g1.globo.com/ap/amapa/noticia/2015/03/centro-de-oiapoque-lidera-casos-de-chikungunya-vitimas-passam-de-2-mil.html [in Portuguese]

[It is odd that a 5 Mar 2015 report in O Globo cites the most recent Ministry of Health Epidemiological Bulletin indicating that so far this year (2015) there are 689 suspected locally acquired cases and 82 confirmed ones, case numbers far fewer than those reported above for Amapa state. - Mod.TY]

Colombia (Barranquilla, Atlantico department. 3 Mar 2015. (reported) 2591 cases.
http://www.eltiempo.com/colombia/barranquilla/campana-contra-chikunguna-y-dengue-/15333355 [in Spanish]

Ecuador
- National. 3 Mar 2015. (registered) 222 cases. Municipality most affected: Esmeraldas 104 cases.
http://www.entornointeligente.com/articulo/5199140/Se-declara-emergencia-en-Esmeraldas-por-brote-de-Chikungunya-03032015 [in Spanish]

- Esmeraldas city, Esmeraldas province. 27 Feb 2015. (conf.) 104 cases. Dramatic increase in cases.
http://www.eluniverso.com/noticias/2015/02/27/nota/4599566/aumentan-104-casos-chikungunya-esmeraldas [in Spanish]

- Quevedo, Los Rios province and Manabi province. 3 Mar 2015. Quevedo (registered) 10 cases. Increasing. Manabi (registered) 25 cases in 2014, 50 cases in 2015.
http://www.eluniverso.com/noticias/2015/03/03/nota/4615311/quevedo-10-casos-chikungunya [in Spanish]

- Viva Alfaro parroquia, Quevedo canton, Los Rios province. 26 Feb 2015. Dengue (reported) 6 cases.
http://www.eluniverso.com/noticias/2015/02/26/nota/4593896/chikungunya-llega-2-provincias [in Spanish]

[Chikungunya virus infections appear to be spreading in Ecuador. One hopes that the epidemiological barriers being put in place around localities where cases have occurred is effective in halting further spread. - Mod.TY]

Paraguay (national). 9 Mar 2015. (conf.) 271 cases; deaths 1. Municipalities most affected: Asuncion 89 cases, Villa Elisa 73 cases, Luque 30 cases, Nemby 25 cases, 13 San Lorenzo 13 cases, Lambare 10 cases.
http://www.sinembargo.mx/09-03-2015/1275646 [in Spanish]

Suriname (national). 3 Mar 2015. (reported) 1210 cases.
http://www.trinidadexpress.com/news/303-cases-of-ChikV-in-TT-294931231.html

Venezuela (national). 4 Mar 2015. The Venezuela government Epidemiological Bulletin of week 07, ending 27 Feb 2015 reports (susp.) 34 642 cases, (conf.) 2303 cases since the beginning of the outbreak in 2014. However these are the same case numbers for Venezuela reported by PAHO as of 29 Dec 2014 and contradict projections made extra-officially by epidemiological experts in Venezuela.
http://www.el-nacional.com/maria_yanes/meses-chikungunya-secuelas_0_584341667.html [in Spanish]

[ProMED would appreciate receiving any updated case numbers that are available for Venezuela. The chikungunya outbreak continues in Colombia, and it seems likely that the outbreak continues in Venezuela as well. - Mod.TY]

Pacific
---
Cook Islands (national). 5 Feb 2015. (conf.) 18 cases -- 2 ex French Polynesia, 1 ex Samoa.
http://www.radionz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/267817/18-confirmed-chikungunya-cases-in-cooks

[A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map showing the location of the Cook Islands in the Pacific can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3222368,4035. - Mod.TY]

Samoa (national). 27 Feb 2015. (reported) more than 4000 cases. The New Zealand rugby team is monitoring this situation because they have a test game there in July 2015.
http://www.sbs.com.au/news/article/2015/02/27/all-blacks-alert-samoa-mosquito-virus

[This is an interesting example of how an outbreak could interfere with an important sporting event.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map showing the location of Samoa in the Pacific can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3222368,41396. Mod. TY]

